<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36185b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36185b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36185b"> 185(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chipboats</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Robert Juet]</font> was an old comrade and early schoolmate of the great Hudson, with whom he often played truant and sailed <mark>chip boats</mark> in a neighbouring pond, when they were little boys; from whence it is said that the commodore first derived his bias towards a seafaring life. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
